A

AcyclicPreferenceReasoner - Class in reasoner
A Preference Reasoner for (T)CP-nets and CI-nets with support for the following reasoning tasks: Consistency: Is the given preference specification consistent (induced preference graph is cycle-free)? Dominance Testing: Does one outcome dominate another with respect to the given preference specification? Next Preferred: Compute a sequence of outcomes in order such that an outcome that comes later in the sequence does not dominate a preceding outcome. Note: Dominance Testing and Next Preferred reasoning tasks work only for consistent (T)CP-nets and CI-nets.
